  "prompt": "Does implementation of uniform civil code effect funeral rites of religion? And how about religious education?",
  "response": "The Uniform Civil Code (UCC) primarily aims to replace personal laws based on religious scriptures with a common set of civil laws for all citizens. Here's how it might affect funeral rites and religious education:\n\nFuneral Rites:\n1. Generally, funeral practices are considered personal religious practices\n2. UCC typically does not interfere with religious funeral rituals\n3. Cremation, burial, or last rites would likely remain within religious discretion\n4. Inheritance and property rights related to funeral arrangements might get standardized\n\nReligious Education:\n1. UCC is unlikely to directly impact religious education\n2. Constitutional right to religious freedom protects religious educational practices\n3. Secular educational curriculum might be more standardized\n4. Religious schools can still teach religious subjects within constitutional boundaries\n5. Focus would be on ensuring equal educational opportunities\n\nKey Principles:\n- Respect for religious diversity\n- Constitutional protection of religious practices\n- Promoting national integration\n- Ensuring gender equality\n- Maintaining individual religious freedoms\n\nThe actual implementation details would depend on the specific UCC draft and legal interpretation. The primary goal is to create a common legal framework while respecting religious sentiments and practices.",
